{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770990929,"nonce":"RGwGG7Z33VL1shl+fkxJudhhkz8=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87qrn3W","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/196","origin":"github"},"title":"docs: CLAUDE.md worktree section lacks project repo workflow and has invalid example","message":"## Problem\n\nThe CLAUDE.md worktree section doesn't adequately explain how to work on **project repos** (repos under `layers/`). This caused an agent to bypass the worktree scripts entirely and use raw `git worktree` commands in `/tmp` when working on a project repo PR.\n\n### Specific gaps in CLAUDE.md\n\n1. **Layer worktree example is invalid** — missing required `--packages` argument:\n   ```bash\n   # Current (broken — missing --packages):\n   .agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh --issue \u003cN\u003e --type layer --layer core\n\n   # Correct:\n   .agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh --issue \u003cN\u003e --type layer --layer core --packages \u003cpkg\u003e\n   ```\n\n2. **No mention of project repos** — the section doesn't explain that layer worktrees create git worktrees *inside* project repos for the specified packages. An agent reading only CLAUDE.md would reasonably assume the worktree scripts only manage the workspace repo.\n\n3. **No project repo example** — there's no example showing the common workflow of working on an issue that lives in a project repo (e.g., `unh_marine_autonomy#57`), including use of `--repo-slug`.\n\n4. **WORKTREE_GUIDE.md is listed as \"Read When Needed\"** — but CLAUDE.md doesn't provide enough context for the agent to realize it needs the guide. The guide does explain project repo worktrees well, but agents following CLAUDE.md's \"all rules are inline\" promise never consult it.\n\n### Impact\n\n- Agent used raw `git worktree add /tmp/...` instead of the managed worktree scripts\n- Worktree was invisible to `worktree_list.sh`\n- No integration with `worktree_enter.sh`, `worktree_remove.sh`, or the scratchpad system\n- Other agents couldn't discover or coordinate around the worktree\n\n### Real-world scenario\n\nWorking on PR #58 of `unh_marine_autonomy` (issue #57 in that repo). The correct command would have been:\n```bash\n.agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh --issue 57 --type layer --layer core --packages helm_manager\n```\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}